                <head>363. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>In mid-August 1957, a crisis in United States-Syrian relations erupted when, in
                    response to Syria’s expulsion of two U.S. diplomats and the Military Attaché for
                    plotting against the Syrian Government, the United States declared the
                    Ambassador and Second Secretary of the Syrian Embassy persona non grata and
                    dispatched <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Loy Henderson</persName> to the Middle
                    East to discuss the Syrian situation with Turkish, Iraqi, Jordanian, and
                    Lebanese officials. For documentation on the Syrian crisis, including
                    discussions with British, Egyptian, and Israeli officials on the subject, see
                        <ref target="frus1955-57v13#pg_632">volume XIII, pages 632</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
